Dow's 39-point drop led by losses for shares of American Express, Goldman Sachs

Dragged down by losses for shares of American Express and Goldman Sachs, the Dow Jones Industrial Average is falling Thursday afternoon. Shares of American Express AXP, -0.53% and Goldman Sachs GS, -0.74% have contributed to the index's intraday decline, as the Dow DJIA, -0.39% was most recently trading 39 points lower (-0.1%). American Express's shares are down $1.74 (1.7%) while those of Goldman Sachs have dropped $2.25, or 1.1%, combining for a roughly 27-point drag on the Dow. Also contributing significantly to the decline are Pfizer PFE, 0.06%, Walmart WMT, -0.46%, and Nike NKE, -0.63%. A $1 move in any of the benchmark's 30 components equates to a 6.86-point swing.

